Registering @{b}telnetd.device@{ub}
==========================

   @{b}telnetd.device@{ub} is shareware.  The demo version of the device is
restricted in several ways (see @{"Creating the configuration file" Link "Creating the configuration file"}).
Registering @{b}telnetd.device@{ub} will provide you with a personalized version
of the device which does not have any of these restrictions.  Supporting the
author will also help to insure that improvements on the device are
made.

   The most recent information on how to register will always be found
in @{b}telnetd.device@{ub}, itself.  To get this information, open the device
with a regular terminal program, open a capture file, and then type
@{b}ATI1 RET@{ub} (1).  You can now close the capture file and print out the
registration form.

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1)  In registered versions of the device, the @{b}ATI1@{ub} command displays
who the device has been registered to.


@EndNode

